MthdOfAmntDtrmntnTxt: The Association of Theological Schools (ATS) is related to the Commission on Accrediting (COA) through overlapping membership. In order to seek accreditation through COA, an institution must first become a member of ATS. Through a support services agreement between ATS and COA, ATS provides personnel, operational, and facility services to COA. ATS charges COA for the direct cost of personnel provided for COA work and for indirect support services. The total charged from ATS to COA was $1,156,022 during fiscal year 2020.
